  {:stage :m5
   :name "external-implementation-suite"
   :status :ambiguous
   :note "kotoba-lang/kototama's src/kototama/aiueos_adapter.clj requires
          `aiueos.cli` and its deps.edn depends on
          io.github.kotoba-lang/aiueos (git@github.com:kotoba-lang/
          aiueos.git) -- NOT io.github.kotoba-lang/aiueos-cljc-contract.
          Investigating found kotoba-lang/aiueos's GitHub repo (the
          'examples/deployment, not authority' repo per ITS OWN README)
          still carries its own src/aiueos/{audit,broker,cli,contract,
          decide,graph,manifest,policy,signing,surface,topic}.cljc --  a
          near-complete but slightly stale duplicate of this repo's src/
          aiueos/ (missing execute.cljc and launcher.cljc, which only
          exist here). So kototama's real dependency target is this
          STALE DUPLICATE living in a different repo than the one whose
          README claims authority, not this repo. This is a genuine
          consolidation gap across the aiueos-cljc-contract / aiueos
          repo split, not something this maturity pass fixes -- flagged
          for a follow-up decision (repoint kototama's dep, or delete
          kotoba-lang/aiueos's duplicate src/aiueos/ now that this repo
          is current). Separately, this investigation also found and
          fixed two local checkouts (orgs/kotoba-lang/aiueos and
          orgs/kotoba-lang/aiueos-cljc-contract) whose `origin` git
          remotes were misconfigured to point at each other's GitHub
          repos -- a plain metadata bug, unrelated to the source
          duplication itself, already corrected."
   :evidence []}
